    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="402"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/9–1544</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Greek Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Reference is made to the memorandum of the Royal Greek Embassy dated September
                    15, 1944,<note n="16" xml:id="d402fn16">Not printed.</note> requesting that the
                    American representatives charged with presenting the armistice terms to Bulgaria
                    be instructed to maintain close contact with the diplomatic representatives of
                    the Greek Government at the place chosen for the armistice discussions.</p>
                <p>The Department of State will have in mind the Embassy’s request when, following
                    the determination of the place and time for the presentation of the armistice
                    terms for Bulgaria, instructions are sent to its representative regarding his
                    participation in the presentation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-21">October 21,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
